@startuml

' E-Home-2020 System Class Diagram

class SensorController {
  + String address
  + Room[] rooms
  + Map<String, Sensor> sensors
  + List<User> users
  + addSensor(sensor: Sensor)
  + removeSensor(sensorId: String)
  + updateSensorDescription(sensorId: String, newDescription: String)
  + assignSensorToRoom(sensorId: String, roomId: String)
  + getSensorValues(sensorId: String): List<Value>
  + getLastValue(sensorId: String): Value
  + setThreshold(sensorId: String, threshold: Double)
  + getThreshold(sensorId: String): Double
  + login(username: String, password: String): User
  + registerUser(username: String, password: String, isAdmin: Boolean): Boolean
}

class User {
  + String username
  + String password
  + boolean isAdmin
  + String email
  + String apartmentAddress
  + List<Room> rooms
  + List<Sensor> sensors
  + querySensorValues(sensorId: String): List<Value>
  + getLastValue(sensorId: String): Value
  + setThreshold(sensorId: String, threshold: Double)
  + setEmail(email: String)
  + getThreshold(sensorId: String): Double
}

class EMonitor {
  + checkThresholds()
  + sendAlertMessage(apartmentAddress: String, message: String)
}

class Sensor {
  + String vendorId
  + String description
  + String unit
  + Room room
  + List<Value> values
  + getValues(): List<Value>
  + getLastValue(): Value
  + getVendorId(): String
  + getDescription(): String
  + getUnit(): String
  + getRoom(): Room
}

class Value {
  + Date timestamp
  + double value
  + getValue(): double
  + getTimestamp(): Date
}

class Room {
  + String description
  + List<Sensor> sensors
  + getRoomDescription(): String
  + getSensors(): List<Sensor>
}

' Associations
SensorController "1" -- "many" Sensor : manages
SensorController "1" -- "many" User : manages
SensorController "1" -- "many" Room : contains
User "1" -- "1" Apartment : belongs to
Sensor "1" -- "many" Value : has
Room "1" -- "many" Sensor : contains
EMonitor "1" -- "1" SensorController : checks thresholds for
EMonitor "1" -- "1" SensorController : sends alerts through

@enduml

### Notes:
- This diagram captures the core entities and their relationships based on the system requirements.
- `SensorController` is the central component managing sensors, users, rooms, and thresholds.
- `EMonitor` interacts with `SensorController` to check thresholds and send alerts.
- `User` can be either a regular user or an administrator, with different capabilities.
- Each `Sensor` has associated `Value` objects for historical data.

